race.comment: ELONIA (9) is an interesting one. She was dominant when winning her maiden first up at Kyneton when scoring by 5.5 lengths but dropped right out to finish a long last at Ballarat in a much stronger race last time. We'd be forgiving of that, plenty of horses struggled on that track and this is much easier. FULLY CALCULATED (5) was just fair last time at Caulfield Heath in a strong BM66 and has been given a freshen up since then. The run two back was good and she can improve. FUROSSHI (4) is a model of consistency, trying hard again at Werribee. 1000m is her best trip and she'll be hard to hold out. SEVEN OCEANS (10) found the line well behind a speedy type at Mornington and can figure off that.
